result.execSummary:
The defendant Jared M. Kearney was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (<120 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(3).
  • Failure to Support Child (<120 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Concurrent with: Concurrent with any other sentence.

miscConds.notes: Defendant shall pay the Court Cost in this matter.

Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and follow through with all recommendations thereof; comply and engage in treatment.
Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcoholic beverages or nonprescription controlled substance, or any prescription medicine for which the defendant does not have a current prescription for.
Defendant shall not enter into any establishment where the primary purpose is the sale of alcoholic beverage.
Defendant shall consent to a reasonable request of a law enforcement officer, based on probable cause, to submit to a breath, blood, saliva, or urine test for purposes of determining the quantity of alcohol or drugs in defendants breath, blood saliva, or urine. 
Defendant shall participate in any and all counseling deemed appropriate by the Division of Community Corrections.
Defendant shall pay child support as ordered in Lafayette County Circuit Court Case No. 15-FA-28.
Defendant shall obtain full time employment or attend school full time or a combination of both; may travel to State of Iowa for employment.
Defendant shall abide by all other terms and conditions of probation deemed appropriate by the Division of Community Corrections.

supervisions.notes: Concurrent with: Concurrent with any other sentence.

miscConds.notes: Defendant shall pay the Court Cost in this matter.
Conditions are the same as in Count One.
